lead_paragraph: A Sports of The Times column on Monday, about the plight of Shahar Peer, the Israeli tennis player who was denied a visa to play in an event in Dubai, misspelled, in some copies, the name of the city in New Zealand where she faced a small protest last month because of Israel’s Gaza incursion. It is Auckland, not Aukland.
